  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Now, those were the times in 1939, with a further deterioration of course, a life that we had in Germany, because now the Germans considered the Jews not only being Jews or enemies of the country, now, they labeled the Jews as traitors.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We obviously have to be identified.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So consequently, we had to wear a star with the word 'Jew' on it, 'Jude' of course, in German, on our left front breast.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes- you-- Yes, the way they were issued was we did have sort of a, supposedly, a-- a Jewish public service building, where a few organizational activities took place.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You couldn't congregate, of course.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The main reason, as I found out many, many years later, was that the main responsibility for this building to be permitted to exist was to consistently have an update where the Jews were living.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
